</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,236,677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="142">
Etymology. The species is named after Mr. Xinxin Zhao (
<collectingRegion box="[806,977,618,642]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="2" pageNumber="142">Inner Mongolia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[989,1057,618,642]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="142">China</collectingCountry>
), who collected the first specimen of the 
<typeStatus box="[176,222,653,677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="142">type</typeStatus>
series and kindly donated it to 
<collectionCode box="[556,636,652,676]" country="China" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crjh-4ne1" name="Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences" pageId="2" pageNumber="142">IZCAS</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
